    "Since the product ξ φ is nonnegative -by the inclusions in (4.33) and the monotonicity of ∂F 1 -we easily derive α 2 ∥µ α (t)∥ 2 + K 2 ∥(1 * µ)(t)∥ 2 V + τ 2 ∥φ(t)∥ 2 + Qt |∇φ| 2 ≤ α 2 ∥µ 0,α ∥ 2 + Qt α ∂ t µ α µ + Ω α µ ′ 0,α (1 * µ)(t) + Qt P (1 * ρ) µ -Qt [1 * ((h(φ α) -h(φ))u 1)] µ -Qt F ′ 2 (φ α) -F ′ 2 (φ) -χ 2 φ φ + Qt χ ρ φ (4.36) for all t ∈ (0, T], where K:= min{P, 1}.",
    "Now, recalling the boundedness properties (4.2) and (4.3), the estimate (4.26) for α 1/2 ∥∂ t µ α ∥ L ∞ (0,T; H), as well as the regularity µ ∈ L ∞ (0, T; H), we deduce from Young's inequality α 2 ∥µ 0,α ∥ 2 + Qt α ∂ t µ α µ + Ω α µ ′ 0,α (1 * µ)(t) ≤ Cα + Cα 1/2 + K 16 Ω |(1 * µ)(t)| 2 + Cα 2 ∥µ ′ 0,α ∥ 2 ≤ Cα 1/2 + K 16 Ω |(1 * µ)(t)| 2.",
    "(4.37) We integrate by parts in time the next two terms on the right side of (4.36).",
